This is another remake of cs_crackhouse,  minus most of its flaws, 
There are two Hostage Rescue Zones now, eliminating the strangle point
at the one HRZ. Game strategies are improved because there are three 
HR routes now not just one. There is a back door, and a basement 
with a sewer area now, which are the other two HR Routes. 
The wooden fence which was transparent to bots is now a brick wall.
There are 95 custom textures/models, and a radar overview place-painted
for enemy troop movement intell when bots are used. The nav file was tuned
for the fastest glitch-free play possible.... ( note Hostages can't use ladders
and have problems going up or down basement steps rescue the basement 
bots through the sewer and the upstairs bots anywhere upstairs)

Map will play very well with Deathmatch mod aswell.

If you downloaded the 2010 version of this map i suggest you delete it and download this one which has many improvements.

Well you've finally died. Finally after so many frags and deaths, you've finally made to the afterlife. The Counter-terrorists have gone to heaven and the Terrorists have gone to hell.

God has helped the CTs by giving them the clouds to walk on and the devil has hid the hostages among the many paths in the firey depths of hell.

But beware, don't fall from the heavens and don't burn in hell. You might take a turn for the worse.

SPAWNPOINTS: 32 terrorist, 32 counter-terrorist, 64 total.

DESCRIPTION:
The terrorists heist of the Harbor Bank has ran into a hitch: they can't get into the vault.  Out of desperation they have taken four bank tellers hostage and demanded no police within one city block.

You are free to navigate a full 360 degrees around the exterior of the bank as you see fit, but beware of long range weapon fire.

If you get pinned down by snipers, you are advised to use the city's underground drainage system to get yourself to a better position.  It has entrances at every corner of the map.

The bank structure itself is the recommended zone for enemy encounterment.  Its upstairs halls and offices should provide sufficient cover for you and your men using even short-range weapons.

The first floor lobby and vault room are more suited for mid-ranged weapons.

The hostage rescue zone is located AT THE HARBOR BOAT DOCKS.  INTEL has determined this is the only feasible escape route to get the hostages to safety.

NOTICE:
Due to the "free-roam" nature of this map and the consistent level of detail, some find that it can run sluggish on slower machines.  I suggest you try lowering your Counter-Strike advanced video settings if you find yourself with unsatisfactory framerates.

Maps Included: cs_halflife_facility, cs_halflife_facility2.

These maps are Half-Life: 1 styled solely indoor worlds built being able to support both human, and CPU players alike. Each map takes place in an unnamed government science facility somewhere in the desert. Affiliation with Black Mesa is neither confirmed nor denied but is easily assumed to be either working with or part of the facility. The only evidence against this theory would be the difference in sector names, equipment, and building patterns examples being Black Mesa using wall stripes to point to a part of the facility while this facility uses wall signs to tell people their exact location in the compound.

Map Type: Hostage Rescue. Including 6 hostages to rescue.

Bugs: On rare occasions, bots will finds themselves stuck behind simple things like a purposely made floor traps, carved brush props, or unclear navigation that confuse bots. Due to extensive play testing and observations of the bots navigating through all pathways, I think it's safe to say that these events are hard to come by.

Miscellaneous Information: Both maps are only able to support 40 players total. If you play the either map with the amount of bots over 39 (Playing Alone), players will begin to spawn inside of other players. Custom sounds and textures are included.

Special Features: On the cs_halflife_facility map, there will be a warning that will sound at the beginning of every match; "Static This is dispatch, be careful with that central power module in the maintenance room. If anything happens to it the whole facility could go BOOM! Static" A testy machine somewhere in the maintenance room that once destroyed will activate a self destruct style sequence. First the lights will go out, all ambient noise will stop, and an emergency notice will blair on the overhead. Shortly after, the entire map will begin rumbling before the sounds of explosions roar. Lastly, everyone on the map will die.

This map is intended to be a sniping map, but I put enough things to hide behind and around to make it a good sneaking and gunning map as well. There are lots of high places (multi-floor towers with elevators to roof, sniper towers, and access to higher areas by ladder) to snipe from. There are also underground tunnels to run through. They lead to the outside bunker and sniper tower for each base, but you can not enter the tunnel in your teams base and make it into the other's base.

Running the hostages to the hostage rescue is a long way, but there are multiple paths to take. I'd recommend staying underground as much as possible, and not trying it unless the Ts are really low in number.

I did create a Nav Mesh for the bots, but I haven't configured it so the can access the moving elevators. I don't know how to or if I even can. They can get to the 4th level of the towers and anywhere else with a ladder, but that's about it. It's enough to get a decent bot game going.

I hope you enjoy the map and please let me know what you think of it. I only want to improve as a mapper and this is the first map I've decided to put online. If you guys think it's worth a damn, some time on a few dedicated servers would be wonderful. You can leave feedback for me on here, but I also have a watermark hidden in the map that has my email address on it.

The CS: Source Sequel to cs_grenadefrenzy!

History:
cs_grenadefrenzy was originally released in September 2001, and was the second map in the first official TJF's Maps 2001 Collection One. The concept was simple; put two teams in a small room with a wall separating each other and have them throw grenades at each other. The rooms were small enough for grenades to land and damage several enemies at once, and players could strategically spy on their opponents through the bulletproof windows in the separating wall. They could then choose to rush with their pistol, or run around throwing grenades whilst dodging incoming grenades.

Players found nothing more satisfying than achieving up to half a dozen kills with one grenade, and cs_grenadefrenzy became a huge success.

Info:
cs_grenadefrenzy2 is a small map with plenty of grenades. You can't buy anything, so you'll have to try rushing over the ladders or walkways into the enemy's side of the map or attempt to grab a grenade before you get blown away by an explosion.

In cs_grenadefrenzy2, there's no such thing as grenade spam.

New Features:
- A complete visual overhaul; greatly improved visual appearance over the original cs_grenadefrenzy.

- Physics enabled structures - map structures react to grenade explosions.

- More player spawns and more grenades than the original cs_grenadefrenzy.
